description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Health and Wellbeing Coach with Lancaster Medical Practice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;HOURS: 37.5 hours per week &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;12 month fixed term contract,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 x roles available&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you passionate about delivering high quality care to patients, and are looking to develop your career in primary care? Then this could be the role for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for Health and Wellbeing Coaches to join our multi disciplinary teams of GPs, Advanced Clinical Practitioners, Clinical Pharmacists and Social Prescribers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will include being responsible for delivering group and one on one sessions to meet with personalised care plans; engaging with patients to support them in taking an active role in their health; providing advice and support for both patients and colleagues. The role will be supported by the Clinical Director of the Primary Care Network, together with our team of Mental Health Nurses and Pharmacists and our Social Prescribers. This is an exciting opportunity to help and make a real difference.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will be proficient, knowledgeable and competent and be able to manage their own workload, as well as build strong relationships. Good communication skills, a flexible approach and good use of initiative are also key.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lancaster Medical Practice is open between 8am and 6.30pm Monday - Friday. Our extended hours provisions run from 6.30pm - 8pm Monday to Friday, and from 8am - 12noon on a Saturday at our Rosebank site.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a team we are made up of a Lead Nurse Partner, ACPs (including a Paramedic, a Physiotherapist and 2 Mental Health Practitioners), Clinical Pharmacists, Practice Nurses, an Assistant Practitioner and a team of HCAs. We work alongside a friendly and dynamic team of GP partners and Associate GPs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LMP offers a range of benefits including NHS pension, a generous holiday entitlement (including Bank Holidays), NHS discounts and offers to name a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please read the attached job description and person specification. Please also take the time to read the attached privacy notice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal chat about this role please contact lmp.hr@gp-p81002.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
